The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Indian eves beat Korea 1-0

 Four-Nation Hockey

 New Delhi: Indian women 

 defeated Korea 1-0 in their first outing of the Four-Nation 

 Junior Field Hockey tournament which began in Gifu in Japan 

 on Wednesday.

 According to information received 

 here, Vinita Xess, after getting a pass from Harpreet, scored 

 the lone goal for India through an indirect conversion of 

 penalty corner.

 India will next meet Malaysia 

 on Thursday and will then take on hosts Japan on Saturday.

 The final as well as the third-place 

 play-off matches will be held on Sunday. 

 (PTI)




